cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with cache-aided device-to-device (D2D) systems, which involve information theory and networking concepts. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the joint design of uncoded cache placement and linear coded D2D delivery, which falls under the category of distributed computing. Hence, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel lower bound on the D2D delivery load, which involves statistical inference and optimization techniques, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper draws connections between cache-aided D2D systems and coded distributed computing (CDC) systems, which falls under the category of coding theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible sub-category.
